---
import Layout from '../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Webcam Eye-Tracking Compendium">
  <div class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl">
          Webcam Eye-Tracking <span class="text-primary-600">Compendium</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          A directory of webcam-based eye-tracking software, libraries, and experiment platforms.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center gap-4">
          <a href={`${base}/tools`} class="btn btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-3">
            Browse Tools
          </a>
          <a href={`${base}/guides`} class="btn btn-secondary text-lg px-8 py-3">
            Guides
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-left">
          <div class="p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Browse Tools</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Explore our directory of webcam-based eye-tracking libraries and software. Compare features, licensing, and platform support to find the right tool for your research needs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Guides</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Step-by-step tutorials for integrating webcam eye tracking into popular research platforms like jsPsych, Qualtrics, oTree, and PsychoPy.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
        <p>
          The rise of autonomous AI agents poses a critical threat to online research. As Large Language Models (LLMs) become capable of mimicking human behavior and bypassing static attention checks, researchers can no longer rely on traditional methods to verify their participants.
        </p>

        <p>
          Based on the idea of <strong>Proof by Presence</strong>, we argue that embedding webcam-based eye-tracking into data collection creates a verifiable physiological signal—a dynamic, moment-to-moment human fingerprint that is difficult for AI to simulate.
        </p>

        <p>
          To make this defense accessible to all, we provide a compendium of open-source tools and guides for integrating webcam-based eye-tracking into research workflows. Our goal is to democratize access to process-tracing technology, allowing researchers to validate human engagement.
        </p>

      </div>

    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Who We Are</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
        This compendium is maintained by researchers committed to preserving the integrity of online research in the age of AI.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-600 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Kianté Fernandez</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">University of California, Los Angeles</p>
          <a href="https://www.kiantefernandez.com" class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-600 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1"> Xiaozhi (Taro) Yang</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">University of Pennsylvania</p>
          <a href="https://xiaozhi2.github.io/" class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-600 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Stephanie Smith</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">University of Chicago</p>
          <a href="https://stephmsmith.com/" class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-600 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Ian Krajbich</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">University of California, Los Angeles</p>
          <a href="https://krajbichlab.psych.ucla.edu/people/" class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
</style>
